---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us — ThinkMode+" description="Learn about ThinkMode+ — the browser extension that automatically enables extended thinking across ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini. Built by AI power users, for AI power users.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="legal-page">

      <h1>About ThinkMode+</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Making AI reasoning the default, not the exception.</p>

      <!-- ── Origin Story ── -->
      <h2>Our Story</h2>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ was born out of a simple, daily frustration. As AI power users, we found ourselves
        doing the same thing every single time we opened a new chat: clicking "think harder," toggling
        extended thinking, flipping reasoning mode on — over and over, across every platform, every session.
      </p>
      <p>
        It seemed absurd. The models are capable of deep, careful reasoning — but they default to
        their fastest guess instead of their best thinking. Every conversation starts at the shallowest
        level unless you manually ask for more. We kept asking ourselves: <strong>why isn't the best
        thinking just… on?</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        So we built ThinkMode+. A lightweight browser extension that silently enables extended thinking
        mode the moment you open ChatGPT, Claude, or Gemini. No clicking, no toggling, no remembering.
        Just better answers from the very first message.
      </p>

      <!-- ── Mission ── -->
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        We believe every AI conversation deserves the model's best reasoning effort — not its fastest
        guess. Extended thinking modes exist because they produce dramatically better outputs: fewer
        hallucinations, stronger logic, more nuanced analysis. But they're buried behind toggles and
        menus that most users never touch.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Our mission is to make AI reasoning the default, not the exception.</strong> ThinkMode+
        ensures that every chat, every prompt, and every session starts with the model's full cognitive
        capabilities engaged. It's a small change with an outsized impact on the quality of every
        interaction you have with AI.
      </p>

      <!-- ── How It Works ── -->
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ operates entirely in your browser. When you navigate to a supported AI platform,
        the extension automatically detects the interface and enables extended thinking / reasoning
        mode in the background — before you even type your first message. It's silent, seamless,
        and requires zero manual interaction after setup.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Automatic activation</strong> — Extended thinking is enabled as soon as the page loads.</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-platform support</strong> — Works across all major AI chat platforms.</li>
        <li><strong>Set-and-forget</strong> — Install once, configure your preferences, and never think about it again.</li>
        <li><strong>Lightweight</strong> — No performance impact on your browsing experience.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── Supported Platforms ── -->
      <h2>Supported Platforms</h2>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ currently supports the three most popular AI assistants — with more on the way:
      </p>

      <div class="platform-grid">
        <div class="platform-card">
          <h3>ChatGPT</h3>
          <p>
            Automatically enables reasoning mode on <code>chatgpt.com</code>. Works with GPT‑4o,
            o1, o3, and all models that support extended thinking.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="platform-card">
          <h3>Claude</h3>
          <p>
            Enables extended thinking on <code>claude.ai</code>. Supports Claude 3.5 Sonnet,
            Claude 4 Opus, and all models with thinking capabilities.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="platform-card">
          <h3>Gemini</h3>
          <p>
            Activates deep-think mode on <code>gemini.google.com</code>. Compatible with Gemini
            2.5 Pro, Ultra, and future reasoning-capable models.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        ThinkMode+ is available as a browser extension for <strong>Google Chrome</strong> and
        <strong>Microsoft Edge</strong>, installable from the Chrome Web Store.
      </p>

      <!-- ── Privacy-First ── -->
      <h2>Built with Privacy-First Principles</h2>
      <p>
        Your conversations with AI are deeply personal — from business strategies to creative
        writing to sensitive research. We built ThinkMode+ with an unwavering commitment to
        your privacy:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Zero data collection</strong> — We don't collect, store, or transmit any of your data. Period.</li>
        <li><strong>No prompt reading</strong> — The extension never reads, logs, or accesses the content of your conversations.</li>
        <li><strong>No analytics or tracking</strong> — There are no analytics scripts, no telemetry, and no usage tracking.</li>
        <li><strong>Local-only operation</strong> — Everything happens in your browser. Nothing leaves your machine.</li>
        <li><strong>Minimal permissions</strong> — We only request the permissions strictly necessary to toggle UI elements on supported sites.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can read our full <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for the complete details.
      </p>

      <!-- ── Get In Touch ── -->
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have questions, feedback, or feature requests? We'd love to hear from you.
        Reach out at <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>, visit our
        <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>, or check out our <a href="/support">Support center</a>
        for help getting started.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .platform-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .platform-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.25s, transform 0.25s;
  }

  .platform-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.4);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .platform-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    background: var(--grad);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .platform-card p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
